The paper discusses the need for efficient source code search engines, which falls under the category of information retrieval (IR) in computer science. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses natural language queries, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is covered in cs.CL. The paper also discusses the challenges of building a universal source code search engine, which involves software engineering (SE) and machine learning (LG) techniques. Finally, the paper discusses the methods for building code search engines, which falls under programming languages (PL).
